description.plain:
Darien Hinton, better known as Mooski, is an American singer and rapper from Opp, Alabama.

Growing up in the local church, he started to work on his talents as part of the choir and, later on, he began his musical career in Gospel rap, being mainly inspired by Christian Hip-Hop veteran Trip Lee.

He also served in the United States' marine for a brief period of time.

After he left the CHH scene, he officially made his debut with the song “Track Star:” originally released in June 2020, Mooski’s first single also turned into his breakout hit, as the track got the most traction since February 2021 after becoming a popular choice on the TikTok platform.

He also served in the United States' marine for a brief period of time.

After he left the CHH scene, he officially made his debut with the song “Track Star:” originally released in June 2020, Mooski’s first single also turned into his breakout hit, as the track got the most traction since February 2021 after becoming a popular choice on the TikTok platform.
